OL,3,CCompany fined for crane collapse that
OL,4,Cput more than 250 people in danger
OL,6,FA dock operator has been fined after a
OL,7,Fcrane collapsed in Cornwall, putting
OL,8,Fmore than 250 people at risk.
OL,10,FEmergency services declared a major
OL,11,Fincident on Falmouth Docks following
OL,12,Fthe collapse of a A&P Falmouth Limited
OL,13,Fcrane on 10 May 2017. The surrounding
OL,14,Farea was evacuated and cordoned off.
OL,16,FThe crane had been operating above the
OL,17,FRoyal Fleet Auxiliary (RFA) ship
OL,18,F'Tidespring', when the driver noticed
OL,19,Fthe jib was descending uncontrollably.
