OL,4,Cput more than 250 people in danger
OL,6,FAlthough it had been examined by a
OL,7,Fthird party, its recommendations
OL,8,Fregarding defects were not acted on by
OL,9,FA&P Falmouth.
OL,11,FA&P Falmouth Limited, of Wagonway
OL,12,FRoad, Hebburn, Tyne and Wear pleaded
OL,13,Fguilty to breaching Section 2(1) and
OL,14,FSection 3(1) of the Health and Safety
OL,15,Fat Work etc. Act 1974.
OL,17,FThe company was fined #750,000 and
OL,18,Fordered to pay #26,792.30 in costs at
OL,19,FTruro Crown Court on 11 October 2024.
